tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All results are within normal limits except for a mildly elevated HbA1c (6.0%), indicating prediabetes, and triglycerides at the upper normal limit. Renal function, electrolytes, and lipid profile are otherwise unremarkable. Recommend lifestyle modification and follow-up for glycemic control. No acute laboratory concerns.
